{
  "stem": "14900.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So we had two double beds.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I slept with my parents, my grandparents, in the other.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And this became our home.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "But as long as my father was there, it was all right.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Then they rounded the men up.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "My father was gone.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "That left myself, my mother, and my grandparents.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Well, I can't tell you the exact dates.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "But August, end of August, maybe first of September-- we always had a knapsack packed, knowing that they came to the homes in the middle of the night and evacuated Jews.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "There was a pounding on the door.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And the German voice was yelling, [GERMAN], which means, out, Jews, fast.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And I think we had a few minutes to pull our clothes on, grabbed our little knapsacks, whatever else we could carry that was ready to go, and at gunpoint were escorted to the church.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And we saw Jewish families from all over town.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "We happened to live almost directly across the street from the church.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "They were all being marched in, taken inside the church.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And I don't know how many hundreds.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "I can't tell you.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "There was barely room for the children to sleep on the wooden pews.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "Most people sat up.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "In the morning, they did permit us to go out into the courtyard.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "The church took up a humongous square block.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And it had a wrought iron, probably three or four foot fence around it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "We could go close to the fence, but never past it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And the Polish Catholics were kept across the street, not just the sidewalk and street, but on the next sidewalk.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And we saw everybody looting our homes, carrying things out, screaming good riddance, just armloads of clothing, furniture, bedding.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't know who they were.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
